	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=795><span id= >Rousch</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Greetings,<br><br>If you are going to hunt in Lavastorm, make sure you have a magical weapon, because if you're hunting the fire elementals, you need on to hit them.&nbsp;&nbsp;At 14th level, hunt near the zone, and bring the mob close there.  Make sure you snare first, then run towards the zone.  Stop every so often to blast the mob, and when he reaches you near the zone, run the other way, away from the zone.  Keep on doing this until he is dead, or you run out of mana, and run near the zone.  Battle him toe to toe, and he should die soon.  If not, and you are getting rocked, zone.  I would recommend grouping with another caster type here or maybe pseudo tank with spell abilities.  Good luck,<br><br>Rousch<br>14th Druid, Lanys Tavyl</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
