<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96655880722472>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=8&mid=96655880722472>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96655880722472>Circle of Death</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96655880722472#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 8:33 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43><span id=Sage>Waeloga</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>56 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.17]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I pick this idea up from EQDruids so no, I don't claim the idea... I do say that it works. Here it is:<br><br>Needed: Outdoor area large enough to run around in<br>You need to be 14th level (SOW) and you need to join up with a Wizard (preferred) or a Mage. <br><br>SOW both of you.... then you go out to find a yellow/red creature, snare it, Swarm it (if snare worked) then run back to your partner. She casts DD spells on the beastie until it turns on her.... then you cast DD spells on it until it turns back on you, then your partner casts DD spells once again, etc, etc. The RUNNER must make sure to stay in the spell range of the caster. <br><br>It works like a treat. You don't need to much room to run around once the beast is snared and being spelled to death. Worked on light reds with it rarely hitting me.<br><br>My thanks to whomever thought it up first<br><br>Waerloga</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
