	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=650><span id= >Tutten</span></a><br><span id=notbold>14 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I died quite a few times in Lavastorm in my teens.&nbsp;&nbsp;But, it was a great place to hunt those levels in spite of the danger.<br><br>First, if you can, find a partner and the danger and downtime is reduced incredibly.  I made a half level in about 90 minutes while grouped with a necromancer there.<br><br>Second, remember to use expulse summoned against fire imps, fire elementals and lava crawlers.  Don't ask me why lava crawlers are summoned (or why rock dervishes aren't!)<br><br>Third, fire elementals sometimes have damage shields of their own.  Porcupining is not a good idea in this case.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>tuttenclawstorm@yahoo.com<br></td></td></tr>
