	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.90]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Most druids dont realize as i run my warrior what couple little used spells used during group.<br><br>1) Snare- Useful if you dont root due to fact that if a mob tends to run away, they act as if rooted with the benefit of not attacking/or snare/fear combo if teamed with a fear user works great as well.&nbsp;&nbsp;To me snare is most useful spell in the game for druids.<br><br>2) Shield of Thorns series- Many times i have grouped with druids who dont cast this type spell on your main taunters/tanks.  Although you do have nukes/heals, that extra 4-29 pts per damage on a mob that hits your main aggressor works wonders on top of your melee/spells.  If for example you use Shield of Thorns/lvl 49-24 pts of damage;  If your tank get double attacked/plus kicked, thats 72 pts of damage/plus spell lasts at least 4 mins plus works on all monsters attacking.  Over time thats as good as some dots per that level you using it.  Please bear that in mind, and thats just an example to be used.  Lower spells do less damage but then your hunting the appropriate level of monster. Save your mana for when it really counts. </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
