	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.17]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;    I agree with the advise given.  Snare/Thorns are the Druid's #1 assests to a group at high levels.  At lower levels, we're effective healers too.   Also, everybody knows this, and if you don't do it, you'll get biched at.... but forget not our SoWs!!<br><br>IMO, our DD spells, in terms of a primary attack, are a jokes, as they take a lot of mana, and don't do enough damage for the ammount of mana they use.  Compared to other classes, our DoTs are laughable (until 52+), and everybody knows that for 40-52, G healing is little more than a mage with an itchy "bind wound" finger.<br> <br>         I don't want to put us down tho.  Dispite the fact that we can't do anything well, we are masters of all.   Our healing will save our groups ass on occasion.   Our DoTs, stacked effectivly, complement other classes' dots.    Our DD help stop that fleeing mob<br><br>         In one of the previous posts, the suggestion was made to use the group damage shields at 51+ in favor of the singular dmg shields.  I'd say only do this in cases where there are 3 or more people in your group that SHOULD be taking hits.  Sure, everybody is going to get hit once or twice, but it is more mana effecient to cast 2 Shield of Thorns than one legacy of spikes, esp if there are only 2 tanks in the group.  It requires less mana, and  Sheild of Thorns does 24 dmg, while Legacy of Spike does 20 i believe.   Keep in mind that some people might not want to have the dmg shiled on them.   I believe that each hp of dmg you do to the mob applies some agro to you.   <br><br>         This means that if a person has a shiled on them, and they get hit, it will develop agro to them.   Monks don't need or want any more agro then they already have, dispite the fact that they are tanks. Rouges don't want it either, as a mob facing them ruins their precious backstab.  Clerics already get beat up enough.  The last thing they need is more to agro 'em.<br>        <br> IMO, shileds should go to: warriors, shadowknights, rangers, pallies, and bards.  (bards can take a few hits, and when their charm breaks, they got one mob all over 'em).<br><br>I look forward to reading other's advice.<br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
